West Pokot governor aspirant Geoffrey Lipale has defected to Kanu, claiming he was rigged out in the Jubilee nominations by incumbent Simon Kachapin.Lipale came second with 29,251 votes against Kachapin's 76,870. But Lipale claimed he has garnered more than 50,000 votes but was rigged out.He said he is bitter about the rigging and will now back Senator John Lonyangapuo &ndash; the Kanu governor candidate.&ldquo;I have decided to decamp from Jubilee and officially join Kanu because I cannot stay in a house with no transparency, no justice, no truth and no democracy,&rdquo; Lipale said. said.